casebody.data:
Tuesday, October 13, 1998

DISCIPLINARY DOCKET

Elsass v. Columbus Bar Assn. Douglas, Acting C.J., Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur. Moyer, C. J., not participating.

98-1909.

On September 16, 1998, appellant, Tobias H. Elsass, filed with this court a notice of appeal and on September 21,1998, appellee, Columbus Bar Association, filed a motion to dismiss appellant’s appeal. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that appellee’s motion to dismiss be, and hereby is, granted, and that appellant’s notice of appeal be, and hereby is, stricken.
